@notice Emitted when credits are removed from circulation without claiming environmental benefit.
 @param  amount Amount of credits canceled.
 @param  reason Reason for credit cancellation.
 @param  creditId ID of the canceled credit.
 @param  account Account that held the canceled credit balance.

@notice Emitted when credits are issued to a new or existing CreditToken contract.
 @param  creditId ID of the credit.
 @param  amount Amount of credits issued.
 @param  to Address of the account that received the credits.
 @param  creditTokenAddress Address of the CreditToken contract.

@notice Issues new credits to a new or existing credit token contract
 @param  creditId The credit ID to deploy 'CMARK-1-2024'
 @param  amount The amount of credits to issue

@notice Cancels a specified amount of credits for a given credit ID and owner.
 @dev    Paused credits can still be canceled.
 @param  creditId The ID of the credit to cancel.
 @param  amount The amount of credits to cancel.
 @param  reason The reason for cancellation.
 @param  owner The address of the account from which to cancel credits.

@notice Pauses the specified CreditToken contract.
 @dev    Paused credits can still be canceled, but not issued.
 @param  creditId The ID of the credit token to pause.

@notice Upgrade CreditTokens by pointing the existing beacon at a new implementation.
 @dev    This upgrades all child credits who were already deployed with this beacon.
         For backwards-incompatible upgrades, see `deployNewBeacon()`.
 @param  creditTokenImpl Address of the new CreditToken implementation

@notice Deploys new UpgradeableBeacon for backwards-incompatable CreditToken upgrades.
 @dev    Only newly issued credits will use this new beacon's implementation.
         Prefer `upgradeBeacon()` instead, if implementation is backwards compatible.
         Or consider deploying a new factory instead.
         After deploying a new beacon, the previous beacon can no longer be upgraded.
 @param  creditTokenImpl Address of the new CreditToken implementation

@title  Factory for CMARK ERC20 credit contracts
 @author Atmosfearful
 @notice The factory is used to:
         - Issue new credits (deploying a new CreditToken contract if needed)
         - Cancel a balance of credits
         - Pause and unpause CreditToken contracts
         - Upgrade the implementation contract for CreditTokens
